===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|quaken}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|cwacian||to quake, tremble, chatter}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*kwakōną||to shake, quiver, tremble}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*gʷog-||to shake, swing}}, related to {{cog|ang|cweccan||to shake, swing, move, vibrate, shake off, give up}} (see {{l|en|quitch}}), <!--{{etyl|frs|-}} {{term|kwakkelje||to flounder, limp|lang=frs}},--> {{cog|nl|kwakkelen||to ail, be ailing}}, {{cog|de|Quackelei||chattering}}, {{cog|da|kvakle||to bungle}}, {{cog|la|vēxō||toss, shake violently, jostle, vex}}, {{cog|ga|bogadh||a move, movement, shift, change}}.

